1. OSI Model Layers & Functions

OSI (Open Systems Interconnection) Model divides network communication into 7 layers.

Layer	Function	Example
7. Application	Provides services to users	HTTP, FTP, SMTP
6. Presentation	Data formatting, encryption	SSL/TLS
5. Session	Creates and manages sessions	NetBIOS
4. Transport	Reliable delivery of data	TCP, UDP
3. Network	Routing and IP addressing	IP, ICMP
2. Data Link	MAC addressing, frame transfer	Ethernet
1. Physical	Physical transmission	Cables, Fiber
Data Flow:

Application → Presentation → Session → Transport → Network → Data Link → Physical

Mnemonic:
All People Seem To Need Data Processing

2. TCP/IP Protocol Suite

TCP/IP is the practical model used on the Internet.

TCP/IP Layer	Function	Protocol
Application	User interaction	HTTP, FTP, DNS
Transport	End-to-end communication	TCP, UDP
Internet	Addressing and routing	IP
Network Access	Hardware transmission	Ethernet
Important Protocols:
TCP → Reliable, connection-oriented
UDP → Fast, connectionless
IP → Addressing
ARP → IP → MAC conversion
Example:

Opening Google:
HTTP → TCP → IP → Ethernet

