8. Hands-on: Encrypt & Decrypt Using OpenSSL
Generate Key
openssl rand -base64 32 > key.txt
Encrypt Message
echo "CyberSecurity" > msg.txt

openssl enc -aes-256-cbc \
-in msg.txt \
-out encrypted.enc \
-pass file:key.txt
Decrypt Message
openssl enc -d -aes-256-cbc \
-in encrypted.enc \
-out decrypted.txt \
-pass file:key.txt

View decrypted text:

cat decrypted.txt

Expected Output:

CyberSecurity
Check Hash

MD5:

openssl dgst -md5 msg.txt

SHA256:

openssl dgst -sha256 msg.txt
